  "sammichesguide1-title": "Sammiches Guide",
  "sammichesguide1-text": "<strong>What is Sammiches?</strong><br><i>Sammiches adds sandwiches, sliced foods, buns, French toast, and other bread-related foods to the game.</i><br><br>Most sandwiches begin with a slice of bread or a bottom bun. Add ingredients one at a time to build your sandwich. A sandwich may hold up to 6 total layers, including the bread or bun used to start it.<br><br><strong>Cutting Board</strong><br>The cutting board is the main work station for crafting sandwiches. You use it to slice bread and ingredients, and build sandwiches.<br><br>Craft a cutting board with 1 board of any wood type in the crafting grid.<br><br><strong>Basic Sandwich Making</strong><br><strong>1. </strong>Place a slice of bread or bottom bun on the cutting board.<br><strong>2. </strong>Hold a valid sandwich ingredient in your hand.<br><strong>3. </strong>Right click the cutting board to add the ingredient.<br><strong>4. </strong>Repeat until the sandwich is finished or reaches the layer limit.<br><strong>5. </strong>Right click with an empty hand to pick the sandwich back up.<br><br>Some ingredients must be sliced before they can be added to a sandwich.<br><br><strong>Slicing Bread</strong><br>Sliced bread is the basis for most sandwiches. Place a loaf of bread on the cutting board, then use a knife or sword on it. One loaf yields 4 slices of bread.<br><br><strong>Slicing Ingredients</strong><br>Some foods, such as vegetables or other solid ingredients, must be sliced before they can be used on sandwiches.<br><br>To slice an ingredient, place it on the cutting board and use a knife or sword on it. If the item can be sliced, the sliced version will be created.<br><br><strong>French Toast</strong><br>You will need:<br><i>1 slice of bread<br>0.1L milk<br>0.1L honey<br>0.1L liquid egg<br>Mixing bowl</i><br><br><strong>1. </strong>Knead milk, honey, and liquid egg together in a mixing bowl to make French Toast Mixture.<br><strong>2. </strong>Knead 0.1L of French Toast Mixture with 1 slice of bread to make French Toast Batter.<br><strong>3. </strong>Heat a clay oven to 170C and place the French Toast Batter inside.<br><strong>4. </strong>Let it bake, then remove it when ready.<br><br><strong>Burger Buns</strong><br>To make burger buns, first prepare normal bread dough or fruit bread dough.<br><br><strong>1. </strong>Hold a bread knife and press F to change the slicing mode to burger bun mode.<br><strong>2. </strong>Place the dough on a cutting board.<br><strong>3. </strong>Use the bread knife on the dough to shape it into burger bun dough.<br><strong>4. </strong>Bake the burger bun dough in an oven until thoroughly baked.<br><strong>5. </strong>Place the baked burger bun on the cutting board and slice it with a knife to create a top bun and bottom bun.<br><br>Use the bottom bun to start marking a burger, then add ingredients as usual. Add the top bun last if desired."
}